# {{NAME}}

A Helios `yield_rotation_v1` strategy built on [`helios-strategy-sdk`](https://pypi.org/project/helios-strategy-sdk/). Scaffolded by `helios scaffold-strategy yield_rotation_v1`.

## Quickstart

```bash
# 1. Install the package + the SDK from PyPI.
pip install -e .

# 2. Backtest your rotation logic against synthetic APY traces. The
#    YR backtest driver lands in WS4 — until then, run the unit test
#    that exercises propose_rotation directly.
pytest

# 3. Copy and fill in the on-chain environment.
cp .env.example .env
$EDITOR .env

# 4. Register on Kite testnet + deploy to your VPS.
helios stake top-up --strategy src/{{NAME_SNAKE}}/strategy.py
helios deploy --strategy src/{{NAME_SNAKE}}/strategy.py --target user@host
```

The whole point of writing your own strategy is the rotation rule —
open `src/{{NAME_SNAKE}}/strategy.py` and edit `propose_rotation`.
The runtime layer (yield-oracle polling, Groth16 proof generation,
`executeWithProof` submission) is in the SDK and does not need to
change.

## What the circuit enforces

`yield_rotation_v1.circom` (`Helios.md §10.4`) commits each rotation to:

  * Both `m_from` and `m_to` are in your allowlist
  * Both APY snapshots are members of the canonical yield-oracle root
  * `apy_to − apy_from ≥ signal_threshold + bridging_cost` (all bps)
  * `m_from ≠ m_to` and `amount_rotating > 0`
  * `block.number ≤ block_window_end`

`signal_threshold_bps` and `bridging_cost_bps` are private witness
inputs. The chain only sees that *some* threshold + budget makes the
rotation consistent.

## Build with Claude Code

This scaffold is set up so an AI coding agent can iterate on the
rotation rule and ship to the marketplace without changing any Helios
code.

In your terminal:

```bash
claude "Open src/{{NAME_SNAKE}}/strategy.py and rewrite propose_rotation \
to favour rotations where the destination market's APY has been above \
its 7-day mean. Add a unit test that pins the choice on a fixed APY \
sequence."
```

The repo's [`CLAUDE.md`](https://github.com/emark-cloud/helios/blob/main/CLAUDE.md) is the canonical operational guide for AI agents working on Helios; class invariants live in `Helios.md §10.4`.

